Allows an alternative GPIO implementation to be supplied on the command line, e.g. for Orange Pi:

    $ sudo python examples/colors.py -f conf/st7735.conf --gpio=OPi.GPIO --spi-port=1

@sgjava & @combs - this should work for your C.H.I.P. board too, by setting `--gpio=CHIP_IO.GPIO`

This incorporates changes from:

@djworth's PR #22
@lisac's PR #29

Plus some, and adds in some additional methods.

fixes #2353

@rhyolight - Does removing the version like this introduce issues? The documentation for namespace packages prohibits anything else from being in the `__init__.py` for a namespace package and [this documentation on version](https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0396/) backs this up.

